                       name="part"
                       a:defaultValue="N">
               <a:documentation>specifies whether or not its parent element is fragmented in some way, typically by some other overlapping structure: for example a speech which is divided between two or more verse stanzas, a paragraph which is split across a page division, a verse line which is divided between two speakers.</a:documentation>
               <choice>
                  <value>I</value>
                  <a:documentation>for the initial part of a container (the end of which is lost or elsewhere) </a:documentation>
                  <value>M</value>
                  <a:documentation>for the medial part of a container (both the beginning and end of which are lost or elsewhere) </a:documentation>
                  <value>F</value>
                  <a:documentation>for the final part of a container (the beginning of which lost or elsewhere) </a:documentation>
               </choice>
            </attribute>
         </optional>
